@node Introduction
    
 What's DeleteSmall ?
   => A file deleting tool !
    
WARNING : Your datas are precious!!!! 
		  Use TEST mode first!! 
    
@endnode

@node Installation
   	
    Just copy DeleteSmall into your C: drawer!
  	
    Remember: USE TEST MODE FIRST!!!
   			Now,  It's NOCASESENSITIVE
   			  
@endnode

@node Usage
    
Available OPTIONS:
    
 {PATH}  (needed): DeleteSmall RAM:
                   => Delete ALL files into RAM:
   	
 MATCHNAME or N:   DeleteSmall RAM: MATCHNAME *.gif
                   (<=> DeleteSmall RAM: MATCHNAME *.gif)
                   (<=> DeleteSmall RAM: N *.gif)
                   (<=> DeleteSmall RAM: matchNamE=*.gif)				    
                   => Delete ALL gifs files into RAM:
   	
 MAXSIZE or - :    DeleteSmall RAM:toto/ - 10000
                   (<=> DeleteSmall RAM:toto/ MAXSIZE 10000)
                   => Delete ALL files of less than 10000 bytes into RAM:toto/
   					
 MINSIZE or + :    DeleteSmall RAM:toto/ + 10000
                   (<=> DeleteSmall RAM:toto/ MINSIZE 10000)
                   => Delete ALL files of more than 10000 bytes into RAM:toto/	
  
 MATCHCOMMENT or N :   DeleteSmall RAM: MATCHCOMMENT *amiga*
                   => Delete ALL  files into RAM: with 'AMIGA' in comment
 
 
 TEST or T      :   don't delete files.
 VERBOSE or V   :   show deleted files.
 ASK or A       :   ask confirmation before delete, 4 options:
                        y  :  delete file.
                        a  :  delete all files.
                        q  :  quit without deleting.
                        n or other : the file isn't deleting.
 RECURSIVE or R :   directory recursive scan.
 RECURSIVELEVEL or L:   set the deep of recursive scan
 DEBUG or D     :   show more informations...
 
  
So, for options madmans:
 
 DeleteSmall HD5:Cache/ MATCHNAME *.jpg MATCHCOMMENT http* + 10000 - 50000 verbose test ask debug recursive l=20 noerror
 
@endnode

